The first settlement in Hope and Caergwrle we are certain of existed at Caer Estyn. Although there have been some suggestions that it is prehistoric, there is overwhelming evidence that the fort originated during Roman times. {(Local history)}
The area became a Christian one in the fifth century when a Saxon church was erected. It was a modest building of wattle and daub.
Although{religion}was a strong feature in the area during Saxon Britain, defence was of paramount importance. The urgency to subdue Welsh attacks into England prompted the construction of Wat's and Offa's Dykes respectively, extensive sections of which can still be seen around the area.
